For an instance that need a restart and there's one or more plugin that are failing to get started, the instance need to be down at least 10 minutes for the timeout countdown to finish.

In most cases, the failed plugin/s would not get started at all after it passed 100 - 200 seconds mark. This is causing unnecessary downtime for an instance.

Plugin timeout for Cloud instances should be lowered from 600 seconds to maybe half - 300 seconds.

